# CLAUDE.md

Working context for Claude Code sessions in this project.

> **What this file is.** The per-project Claude session contract —
> seeded once by a domain Element's `bin/init` at install time and
> never overwritten. Edit freely; the project owns it forever. The
> Element that governs this project (name, version, pinned SHA) lives
> in `.claude/rasa.lock.json` — this file deliberately does **not**
> hardcode it, so it can't drift out of date.

## Who you are (read first)

Your full identity is in two files (canon SA-025):
- **`.claude/rasa-identity.md`** — the RasaOS + element layer, regenerated by
  `bin/init` on every install (who the installed Element is).
- **`.claude/rasa-deployment.md`** — the deployment layer, **project-owned**:
  what THIS project is, for whom, on what platform. **Fill it in.**

Run **`/whoami`** for the composed one-line identity (e.g. *"I am a RasaOS domain
for coding an iOS product for a company called VSI"*).

