## Keeping the installed Element up to date

The Element is pinned by SHA in `.claude/rasa.lock.json`. To absorb
upstream changes:

- If the installed Element ships a **`/sync`** skill (the domain-core
  starter layer provides one), run it — it reconciles installed content
  against upstream, respects your recorded overrides, and advances the
  pin. Never auto-commits.
- Otherwise, pull manually from the repo in
  `.claude/rasa.lock.json#element.repo` and update the pin yourself.

Local edits to installed Element files should be recorded in the
lockfile's `overrides[]`, or they'll be treated as drift on the next
sync.

